                        Tithe/Tax System Description
                      ===================================


Introduction:
------------

The tithe/tax (known as the tithe system from now on) is to be
used by any guild making compulsary donations to a central
coffer or pool for later use.  This can easily be adopted for 
use by a city for a taxation system, by simply adding to the
central coffer when a purchase is made.


Concepts
--------

All functions are held within the TITHE_D system and any
command written to utilize the system should also include
the <tithe.h> header.  

Each coffer or pool has an identifier set up by the #define
TITHE_ID.  This define will be the key for which all 
transactions are referenced and needs to be defined in
a seperate header for that guild/city or within the command
itself.

Once money is donated into a coffer, requests can be made
to withdraw money from the coffer.  That request has to
be approved by an IMP+ before the permitted offical can
then withdraw from the coffers.

Basic Functionality
-------------------

Adding money:

void add_tithe(string TITHE_ID, int AMOUNT)
- This puts money into the coffers
- Also logs an entry into /log/tithes/TITHE_ID.o

Viewing balances:

int query_tithe(string TITHE_ID)
- Returns the int of the total in TITHE_ID's coffer

Withdraw requests:

int withdraw_tithe_request(string TITHE_ID, int AMOUNT, 
			string REASON)
- Adds a request for withdraw, added to the main array
for TITHE_ID

int query_withdraw_request(string TITHE_ID)
- Will return a formated listing of current tithe withdraws
on the books.

Approval/Denial/Removal:

int approve_withdraw_request(string TITHE_ID, int REQUEST_NUM,
			(string APPROVAL)
- This function allows an IMP+ to approve/deny/remove the
request.  APPROVAL must equal either "approve", "deny" or
"delete".  It is up to the coder to decide how to present
these options to the user.  A log entry is made to
/log/tithes/TITHE_ID.approve.o for this transaction.
 
Withdraw:

int withdraw_tithe(string TITHE_ID, int REQUEST_NUM)
- Providing the request has been approved by an IMP+ the
appropriate offical can then finally withdraw the amount
from the coffer to his/her pocket.  A log entry is made
to /log/tithes/TITHE_ID.withdraw.o on the transaction.


EXAMPLES
-------

These examples will show some basic uses of the above
functions.  The first example will show how to put
money into the account, and the next will show a command
to request a withdraw then we show how to list the open
withdraw requests and lastly code to show approval.

Adding tithes
-------------
#include <mudlib.h>
#include <tithe.h>
#define TITHE_ID "myguild"

int do_command(int iAmount) {

  TITHE_D->add_tithe(TITHE_ID,iAmount);
  write("Thanks for your donation.\n");
  return 1;
}

// End Add

Request withdraw
----------------
#include <mudlib.h>
#include <tithe.h>
#define TITHE_ID "myguild"

int do_command(string sRequest){
  int iTithes;
  string sReason;
  int iAmount, iRequest;

  if(!sRequest) {
	notify_fail("Please put the amount then the\
reason in your request.\n")
	return 0;
  }
  if(sscanf(sRequest,"%d %s",iAmount, sReason) == 2) {
	TITHE_D->withdraw_tithe_request(TITHE_ID,iAmount,sReason);
	return 1;
  }
  notify_fail("Please put the amount then the\
reason in your request.\n")
  return 0;
}

// End Request withdraw

Tithe/Tax listing
-----------------

#include <mudlib.h>
#include <tithe.h>

#define TITHE_ID "myguild"

int do_command() {
  int iTithes;

  write("Pending withdraw requests for "+capitalize(TITHE_ID)+":\n");
  TITHE_D->query_withdraw_request(TITHE_ID);
  return 1;
}

// End Tithe/Tax listing

Request approval
----------------

#include <mudlib.h>
#include <tithe.h>

#define TITHE_ID "myguild"

int do_command(string sArg) {
  string sCommand;
  int iInt;

    if(sscanf(sArg,"%d",iInt) != 1) {
        notify_fail("Try tapp <request number>\n");
        return 0;
    }
    if(!iInt) {
        notify_fail("Try tapp <request number>\n");
        return 0;
    }
    TITHE_D->approve_withdraw_request(TITHE_ID, iInt, "approve");
    return 1;
}

// End Request approval

